race.comment: DUAL PRESSURE (3) ticks plenty of boxes here and looks the one. He's in winning form and looks well-placed on the seven-day back-up dropping from 59.5kg to 53kg. From barrier two, he maps to find a position on speed and will take plenty of catching. He's a horse on the up. STIRRUP CUP (5) wasn't far off DUAL PRESSURE last start. While he meets him slightly worse at the weight, he will appreciate getting onto the main track and Morphettville, which should allow him to use his brilliant turn of foot. He can be finishing over the top of them. SHISUTA BO (7) has drawn wide but will roll forward and take some catching. HARD PRINCE (9) looks ready to win after showing form in strong races, while TOSEN WATER (4) looks an each-way chance and must go into exotics and wider plays.
